# NOTE: Product Price IDs are now fetched dynamically from Stripe!
# You no longer need to set individual price ID environment variables.
# The system will automatically fetch all active products and prices from your Stripe account.
#
# To organize your products in the dynamic catalog, use these metadata fields in Stripe Dashboard:
# - plan_id: Unique identifier for the plan (e.g., "essential", "growth", "pro-enterprise")
# - plan_type: Type of plan (default: "subscription")
# - display_order: Order to display products (lower numbers first)
# - features: JSON array of features (e.g., ["Feature 1", "Feature 2"])
#
# Example product metadata in Stripe Dashboard:
# plan_id: essential
# plan_type: subscription
# display_order: 1
# features: ["Basic support", "Up to 100 connections", "Mobile app access"]

